ActionBarManager
Solves the problem of handling multiple actionbars at once.
With Audience.sendActionBar(Component), one actionbar would remove another actionbar.
With the ActionBarManager, it is possible to display multiple actionbars at once.

EventListenerManager
Dynamically manages event listeners.
Instead of directly registering event listeners to Bukkit, listeners are registered to a ListenerOwner.
The ListenerManager then keeps the listeners registered as long as the ListenerOwner provides them.
If not, they are unregistered.
Listeners which should not be managed by this manager has to be excepted.
ExtendedListenerOwnerSource
An ExtendedListenerOwnerSource is a ListenerOwnerSource with the difference that it can provide multiple listener owners.

ManagedEntity<ENTITY_TYPE>
This class provides a manager for entities.
It allows to schedule tasks for entities and works as managed listener.
The goal of this class is to allow scheduling tasks and listen to events while the entity is alive, and then auto-cleanup tasks and listeners when the entity is dead.
DO NOT REGISTER THIS ENTITY DIRECTLY TO THE BUKKIT EVENT LISTENER!!!

SubcommandCommand
A command that can has multiple commands as subcommands.
You can add subcommands with SubcommandCommand.addSubcommand(String, SubcommandEntry).
You can remove subcommands with SubcommandCommand.removeSubcommand(String).
You can set a global permission for the command in the constructor
You can set a DynamicSubcommandProvider that can provide subcommands dynamically in the constructor.
You can override SubcommandCommand.onExecutionWithoutSubcommand(CommandSender, Command, String) to run code when the command is executed without subcommands.
You can override SubcommandCommand.onExecutionWithoutPermission(CommandSender, Command, String, String[], String) to run code when the sender does not have the permission for the command.
You can override SubcommandCommand.onExecutionWithUnknownSubcommand(CommandSender, Command, String, String[]) to run code when the given subcommand does not exist.
SubcommandCommand.PermissionProvider
Provides the permission for the command.
This allows for dynamically providing a permission instead of the permission string.
SubcommandEntry
A subcommand entry represents one command that was added to SubcommandCommand.
